{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "09", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "05", "M": "52", "S": "57"}}, "news": [{"title": "Amazon Seller Services leases over 4.17 lakh sq ft warehouse in Bhiwandi near Mumbai", "para": "Amazon India has taken a warehousing facility in Bhiwandi through a long-term lease, set for nine years beginning June 2026. The financial commitment involves a monthly rent exceeding Rs 1.27 crore. This strategic move highlights Amazon's commitment to enhancing its logistics infrastructure and fortifying its supply chain.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/allied-industries/amazon-expands-logistics-network-with-major-warehouse-lease-in-bhiwandi/132276552?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-163522/132276552.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "allied-industries"}, {"title": "DPCC rolls out Dust Portal 2.0 to tighten monitoring of construction-related pollution in Delhi", "para": "Delhi construction projects must now submit compliance reports and install air quality sensors.  The upgraded Dust Portal 2.0 requires live camera feeds for real-time pollution monitoring.  Projects over 500 square metres must register and map site boundaries using GIS technology.  Self-audit reports covering 12 parameters will be submitted every 15 days.  This initiative aims to strengthen oversight and reduce dust emissions from construction activities.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/delhis-dpcc-launches-dust-portal-20-to-combat-construction-pollution/132276503?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1562418/132276503.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "NGT seeks response from CAQM, others on builder's plea against closure notice", "para": "The National Green Tribunal is reviewing a Haryana construction company's appeal.  This appeal challenges a closure notice issued by the Commission for Air Quality Management.  The company previously challenged this notice before the Punjab and Haryana High Court.  That court dismissed the challenge as withdrawn after granting interim protection.  The tribunal has now issued notices to the relevant authorities for their responses.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/ngt-seeks-response-from-caqm-on-builders-appeal-against-closure-notice/132276217?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-100047/132276217.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}